=== 8.5 The Code: FFN in Python

GELU is the activation function used in GPT-2.
For large positive stem:[x], GELU approaches stem:[x] — the value passes through.
For large negative stem:[x], it approaches 0 — the value is suppressed.
`gelu_matrix` applies the scalar GELU to every element of a matrix.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=activations]
----

`add_bias` broadcasts a bias vector stem:[b] across all rows of a matrix stem:[M].

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=add_bias]
----

`FeedForward` holds the four parameters; `make_feed_forward` allocates them — stem:[W_1] expands the model dimension stem:[d] to stem:[4d]; stem:[W_2] contracts it back.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=make_feed_forward]
----

`feed_forward` composes the two linear layers with GELU: expand → activate → contract.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=feed_forward]
----

